on, chillies, fresh coriander, mint, lemon juice and salt into mixing bowl and chop <b>7 sec\/speed 5<b>. Place simmering basket over a bowl and transfer mixture into it. Set aside to drain."},{"content":"Place lamb, pepper, cumin seeds, ground coriander, turmeric, garlic paste and ginger paste into mixing bowl and cook <b>10 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>, <strong>without measuring cup<\/strong>."},{"content":"Add garam masala and reserved onion mixture and combine <b>30 sec\/\/speed 1<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside to cool slightly."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Assembly"},{"content":"Line a baking tray (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside. Transfer chilled pastry onto silicone bread mat or floured work surface. Divide pastry into 3 equal portions. Using a rolling pin, roll out each portion into a thin rectangle (64 x 18 cm, approx. 1 mm thickness). Cut each rectangle into 8 strips (8 x 18 cm), creating 24 pastry strips in total."},{"content":"Place 1 tablespoon samosa filling at the top of each pastry strip. Fold top left corner of pastry strip diagonally to the right, enclosing filling and forming a triangle. Fold again (folding down) along bottom crease of triangle. Keep folding, creating triangles, to the bottom of the strip. Using your fingertips, dampen remaining pastry edge with water, then fold over to close and seal samosa. Set aside on prepared tray and cover with kitchen towel. Repeat with remaining pastry strips and samosa filling (makes approx. 24 samosas in total)."},{"content":"Line a large plate with paper towel and set aside. Place a large saucepan over high heat and add oil. Heat oil to 170°C (see Tips). Working in batches, carefully place 4-5 samosas into hot oil using a slotted spoon and fry for 7-10 minutes, turning once during frying, until golden brown and crispy. Using a slotted spoon, carefully transfer samosas onto lined plate. Serve with chutney of choice (see Tips)."}],"hintsAndTricks":["You can replace the lamb with minced chicken or beef, or make vegetable samosas by using the Bombay aloo recipe on this recipe chip as a vegetarian filling option.","To make your own ghee, garlic paste, ginger paste and garam masala, please refer to the recipes on this recipe chip.","To check your oil is at 170°C, use a thermometer or drop a small cube of bread into the oil; bread will turn golden brown in 20 seconds at 170°C.","We served these samosas with the Tomato chutney and Tamarind chutney (please refer to the recipes on this recipe chip), but you can pair with any chutney of your choice."],"basicInfo":["medium","1h","1h 35m","24 portions"]}